President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. Margaret Louise Cummisky is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Legislative and Intergovernmental Affairs at the Department of Commerce. Michael Yudin is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Special Education and Rehabilitative Services at the Department of Education. Matthew Winthrop Barzun is nominated for Ambassador to the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland. John Hoover is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Sierra Leone. Crystal Nix-Hines is nominated for United States Permanent Representative to the United Nations Educational, Scientific, and Cultural Organization. John R. Phillips is nominated for Ambassador to the Italian Republic and the Republic of San Marino. President Obama expressed his pride in having experienced and committed individuals serving the American people in these important roles.